Agentic AI Portfolio — Sudipta Chakraborty
==========================================

This repository contains my hands-on implementations of the eight projects
from "AI Engineer Agentic Track: The Complete Agent & MCP Course" by
Ed Donner on Udemy.

Substantial portions of the source code are derived from Ed Donner's
publicly available companion repository at https://github.com/ed-donner/agents
(MIT License, Copyright (c) 2025 Ed Donner). The original LICENSE file is
preserved in this repo as `LICENSE.upstream`.

What I have done in this repository:
  * Restructured the six course weeks into eight self-contained, named
    projects with their own READMEs and run instructions.
  * Authored top-level and per-project documentation, deployment guides,
    architecture diagrams, and Hugging Face Space configurations.
  * Replaced personal data files (the `me/` directory in the original
    Career Digital Twin) with templates so each user can plug in their own
    bio and CV.
  * Added `.env.example` files and explicit secret/key handling notes.
  * Added small extensions and quality-of-life changes (documented per
    project in each README's "My additions" section).

Use of frontier-model APIs (OpenAI, Anthropic, Google Gemini, etc.) is
subject to the providers' terms of service and incurs their charges; you
must supply your own API keys.

This is a learning portfolio, not production software.
